children.subject: I feel like it is doable, with the only exception that CS188 will require some knowledge of CS70 probability

history.content:
Will be tougher than your past semesters, but doable. Math 110 is more proof-based than any of the classes you've taken so far, so it will require a different level of mathematical maturity in my opinion.

I would be careful of Math 53 + CS 70. Both are very fast paced math classes, and require quite a bit of work every week. Overall, I'd say the courseload is quite tough (I personally wouldn't do it) but could be very rewarding if you enjoy proof-based math.

What do you guys think about the following schedule:
CS 70 + Math 53 + CS 188 + Math 110 + AC (will likely P/NP)
Have been taking 20 units for the past two semesters, which went well, might have been easier classes though. However, I did very well in all of them (including Math 1AB, CS 61AB, EE 16A).
history.subject: Fall schedule: Thoughts?
